features: Portable and 5 Mins Setup - This projector tripod comes with a pre-installed structure, making it easy to set up in just 5 minutes. The projector stand features a twist-to-open frame for convenient storage and transport. With its foldable design, it minimizes storage space, making it perfect for outdoor movies, travel,on-the-go meetings and various activities.

6-Height Adjustment for Better Viewing - The projector tripod stand offers 6 height settings from 22.44″ to 36″ tall with a steel pin that locks the pole in place, ensuring secure stability for your electronic equipment. The telescopic pole on the adjustable projector stand operates with a knob lock that makes extension and collapse a breeze.

Flexible 45° Tilt Up Options - The laptop stand includes an extra-large 16″ x 11″ platform to provide more space than average stands. It compatible with most projectors on the market and laptops less than 16 inches. The projector tray can be tilted -5° to +45°, allowing you to adjust the angle for your need with projector or laptop. 0.39″ raised tray edges keep your equipment in place on the platform without sliding off.

22 lbs Heavy Duty Design - The fram of our projector holder is made of sturdy metal material and the feet feature anti-slip rubber pads, capable of supporting weights of up to 22 lbs. This outdoor projector stand can accommodate not only portable projectors but also larger devices. The sturdy triangular base incorporates reinforced braces, ensuring it won't topple even in strong winds.

Multipurpose Stand Meet All Your Needs - This portable projector stand is designed for professional projector support and can also serve for laptops, music sheets, tablets, DJ racks, and more. The laptop stand enables you to use your projector or laptop for everyday entertainment, meetings, presentations, and even as an camping projector stand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for outdoor movies
reviews.reviewText: I recently decided to upgrade my entire outdoor movie setup. New projector, new screen, new sound system. In the past I have used an old Black & Decker Workmate to put the projector on along with the amplifier. It works but, it's a pain to get out because of where it's stored. I saw this stand and decided to try it out. It works perfectly and required minimal assembly (literally just attaching the top tray). Much easier that what I was using. The height and viewing angle are adjustable as well and the tray is wide enough that it holds the projector and the remotes. I deducted one star because it's not the sturdiest tray. If you bump it the tray will jiggle. Overall I'm very happy with the stand and, short of someone falling on it and breaking it, I see no reason why it won't serve my needs for quite some time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is the Best Thing Ever...
reviews.reviewText: Okay. So if you are reading this needing to know if it is good/bad for what it was intended for - then skip this review. My review is based on the need to have something to place my laptop on while I sit on my LoveSac to watch my streaming shows without having to hold the laptop on my lap or place it precariously on the beanbag chair - all the while worrying I am getting something not-so-good-for-me radiating into my legs/abdomen or an other part of my body (with my device so close to me). This enables me to watch my shows from a distance, as if my laptop were mounted on the wall like a real flat screen. I can move it with ease wherever and whenever I need to move my body to change position without having to change anything on the stand - which by the way, there are so many variances with height adjustment, angle, etc. The actual part that the laptop sits on can rotate 360 degrees with ease without compromising stability. All I can say is this: I have not been so stoked with a product since I came across this item in a very long time. Super easy to assemble (part of the tripod stick portion nestles into the main rod, so remember to pull it out to access it, don't call the company like I did stating a missing part) and worth every penny. To the company who makes this - KUDOS. And to all you people out there who use your laptop to stream your shows with - who lounge on a bed or a couch or anywhere else... this is a MUST.
